                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/216.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Train bearing about 700 Spaniards arrived in Juarez this morning. Are all passing
                    quarantine station now. No difficulties were encountered en route. All
                    Government departments are facilitating their entrance to El Paso. Many of them
                    will be in great need and some are almost destitute. What can I do to assist
                    them? They all know me and look to me for assistance and advice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
